an style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ahmad, Asam. (March 2, 2015) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://briarpatchmagazine.com/articles/view/a-note-on-call-out-culture\">| \"A Note on Call-Out Culture\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Briarpatch\" title=\"Briarpatch\">Briarpatch</a></i> Magazine. Retrieved August 3rd, 2018.  </span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Hamad, Ruby, and Liddle, Celeste. (11 October 2017) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/oct/11/intersectionality-not-while-feminists-participate-in-pile-ons\">| \"Intersectionality? Not while feminists participate in pile-ons\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i>. Retrieved August 3rd, 2018. </span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Call-out_culture&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\">Friedersdorf, Conor (May 8, 2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/05/call-out-culture-is-stressing-out-college-students/524679/\">\"The Destructiveness of Call-Out Culture on Campus: Reflections from undergraduates of the social media era\"</a>. <i>The Atlantic</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">October 21,</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle